# Possible Shadow Credentials Added to Active Directory Object
 
Detects the possible addition of shadow credentials to an Active Directory object by monitoring for **Event ID 5136** (Directory Service Changes) where the `msDS-KeyCredentialLink` attribute is modified. This attribute is abused in shadow credential attacks to establish persistence and gain unauthorized access via PKINIT.
 
---
 
## Use Case
 
It is possible to add "Key Credentials" to the `msDS-KeyCredentialLink` attribute of a target user or computer object and then perform Kerberos authentication as that account using PKINIT. Tools like [Whisker](https://github.com/eladshamir/Whisker) can be used to generate and add new key credentials to a target object the attacker has write access over.
 
